commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to handle errors

commitResults.messageBody:
Duke is unable to save the task list on the local computer itself.

The software might crash and cause data to be lost. Thus a backup
is needed.

Save the task list on the local computer serves as a backup in case
data is lost.

Saving the task list on the local computer is convenient and
also reliable.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to process date and times
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke only sees date and time as just a string.

If duke can understand date and times properly, more advanced features
can be implemented.

Implement date in Duke as a java.time.LocalDate object.

Choose java.time.localDate as it has all the necessary features.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Fixed some typos in error messages

commitResults.messageBody:
Duke's ability to parse commands is very basic.

More advanced parsing features allow duke to understand commands better.

Implement a new Parser class to improve Duke's parsing ability.

Creating a separate Parser class adheres to OOP principles and makes
code more readable.

Duke's task processing and file processing features are very basic.

We extend Duke's functionality by adding more task processing and file
processing features.

Implement 2 new classes Storage and TaskList.

Creating separate classes for each function adheres to OOP principles
and makes code more readable.

Duke's Ui features are very basic.

We extend Duke's functionality by adding more Ui features.

Implement a new Ui class to handle Ui features.

Creating separate classes for each function adheres to OOP principles
and makes code more readable.

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: Organise classes into one main package
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke's classes are not organised into packages.

Difficult to manage a large number of classes without packages.

Organise the classes into packages.

We can put related classes in the same package, making managing classes
easier.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JUnit tests for Parser Class
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke currently does not have tests for Parser Class.

There is a high chance a bug may occur in the Parser class in the
future, when new code is added.

Implement JUnit tests to ensure that the Parser class still functions
correctly after future changes.

JUnit tests were chosen due to their convenience.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add more JUnit tests for Parser class

commitResults.messageBody:
The code for Dukebot have no JavaDoc comments.

This makes certain parts of the code difficult to understand.

Add JavaDoc comments for better readibility.

Some parts of the code did not follow the standard coding style.

This makes certain parts of the code difficult to understand.

Standardise coding for better readibility.

Duke does not have the ability to search task by keyword.

When there are a large number of tasks, finding a specific task can be
very tedious.

Implement find method to quickly find specific tasks by keyword.

Users can thus easily find specific tasks, even if there are a large
number of tasks.

Duke project builds are not automated.

As the codebase gets larger, building Duke manually every single time
gets too time-consuming.

Automate build process of Duke using Gradle.

This speeds up the build process via automation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Rewrote code that violates Checkstyle

commitResults.messageBody:
Duke does not have currently have a GUI.

Duke feels bland and boring.

Add a Graphical User Interface to Duke.

Makes Duke more graphically pleasing.

The GUI for Duke is not implemented using FXML.

Creating a GUI is long and tedious as it requires many lines of code.

Implement GUI using FXML.

Makes implementing a GUI faster and easier as FXML is more concise.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Improve code quality and add more comments

commitResults.messageBody:
There are no assertions in the codebase for dukebot.

As the codebase gets larger and larger, having no assertions may make
the program more difficult to debug.

Add assertions to the codebase of dukebot.

This helps us narrow down on the things to look out for when debugging

Duke does not currently have the function of sorting tasks.

This makes it difficult to keep track of certain tasks, especially when
the number of tasks get very large.

Implement the ability to sort tasks based on certain criteria.

Enable users to keep track of more important tasks easily.
